            <p>
                <blockquote cite="https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_quotation_elements.asp"> <q>The HTML address tag defines the contact information for the author/owner of a document or an article.</q> <br>

                    The contact information can be an email address, URL, physical address, phone number, social media handle, etc.<br>
                    
                    The text in the <address> element usually renders in italic, and browsers will always add a line break before and after the <address> element.</blockquote>
